<article>
    <h1>Rules for stay&#xAD;ca&#xAD;tions at ho&#xAD;tels</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201118/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-11-18"><time>2020-11-18</time></a>
        - <span>SINGAPORE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Stay­ca­tions are al­lowed at ho­tels ap­proved by the Sin­ga­pore Tourism Board and Min­istry of Trade and In­dus­try.</p>
    <p>The ho­tels must com­ply with ex­ist­ing safe man­age­ment mea­sures, such as the wear­ing of masks and prac­tice of safe dis­tanc­ing in pub­lic and com­mon ar­eas.</p>
    <p>Gath­er­ings, even those in pri­vate rooms and ad­join­ing rooms, must be lim­ited to five per­sons or fewer.</p>
    <p>The ex­cep­tion is if the gath­er­ing con­sists only of peo­ple who have al­ready been liv­ing in the same house­hold, each with the same ad­dress.</p>
    <p>All ho­tel guests are re­quired to reg­is­ter them­selves and use SafeEn­try for en­try and exit. The use of TraceTo­gether is en­cour­aged.</p>
    <p>There must be stag­gered tim­ings for guests to be at the ho­tel lobby and at guest fa­cil­i­ties, as well as em­ploy­ees at the back-of-house work en­vi­ron­ment.</p>


